  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u2019\u2019\u0d9c\u0ddd\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0dbb\u0d82\u0da2\u0dd2\u2019\u2019  \u0dc3\u0dc4 \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0ddd\u0daf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dad\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0d9c \u0db8\u0dcf\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd6",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"Gorilla Ranji\" and his brother were killed with drugs",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Police Special Task Force says that two brothers from the same family, who are the two main disciples of Sinnaiya Gunasekaram or Kimbulale Guna, a leader who runs the organized crime and drug network, have been arrested along with a consignment of drugs worth nearly 8 lakh rupees.",
        "Police say that the arrested are Ratnam Ranjith Kumar alias \"Gorilla Ranji\" and his brother.",
        "The police have taken 74 880 mg of drugs in the possession of those persons.",
        "The police say that Ratnam Ranjith Kumar aka \"Gorilla Ranji\" runs the drug network of Sinnaiya Gunasekaram aka Kimbula Ale Guna Nematta, an organized crime gang leader who was arrested in a joint operation conducted by the security forces of South India and Sri Lanka.",
        "According to the information received by the officers of the Police Special Task Force Organized Crime Unit 2, a team of officers including the Station Commander Police Inspector CR Paramullage arrested the two suspects during a raid in Madampitiya area of \u200b\u200bBlumandel Police Domain.",
        "On the twelfth last day in Madampitiya area, the police said that it was revealed that Ratnam Ranjith Kumar aka Gorilla Ranji had given instructions to shoot and kill a man named Pradeepan who was riding a motorcycle with his wife.",
        "Police also believe that the brother of the arrested gorilla Ranji is a resident of Ganemulla.",
        "According to the orders and instructions of the Police Special Task Force Commanding Officer, DIG Advocate Mr. Warna Jayasundara, a team including the Station Commander of the Special Task Force Organized Crime Unit 2, Police Inspector CR Para Mullage, arrested the suspects."
      ],
